Class AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eng.util.TaggedEntity
      • org.eng.aisp.classifier.AbstractClassifier<WINDATA>
        • org.eng.aisp.classifier.AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IFixedClassifier<WINDATA>, ITaggedEntity
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FixedAnomalyDetectorClassifier, FixedCNNClassifier, FixedFeatureGramClassifier, FixedGMMClassifier, FixedKNNClassifier

    public abstract class AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier<WINDATA,FDATA>
extends AbstractClassifier<WINDATA>
implements IFixedClassifier<WINDATA>
    Extends the super class to implement classify(IDataWindow). classify(IDataWindow) is implemented by first extracting the features and then calling #classify(IFeature) which must be implemented by subclasses.
    Author:
    dawood

      • AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier

        public AbstractFixedFeatureExtractingClassifier(List<IFeatureGramDescriptor<WINDATA,FDATA>> featureGramExtractors)
        Parameters:
        extractor - the single feature extractor applied to the data
        processors - the 0 or more feature processors applied to the extracted features. Each produces a single IFeatureGram.
        windowSizeMsec - sub-window size on which features are extracted to produce the feature gram across the whole window of data.
        windowShiftMsec - the window shift of sub-windows. 0 means rolling windows (i.e. no overlap).
